mop /mɒp/

(mopping,mopped,mops) 

1. N-COUNT A mop is a piece of equipment for washing floors. It consists of a sponge or many pieces of string attached to a long handle. 拖把 

2. V-T If you mop a surface such as a floor, you clean it with a mop. 用拖把擦 

例： There was a woman mopping the stairs. 有个女人正在拖楼梯。 

3. V-T If you mop sweat from your forehead or mop your forehead, you wipe it with a piece of cloth. 擦拭 

例： He mopped perspiration from his forehead. 他擦去额头上的汗水。

